Bashir Ahmad, Personal Assistant on New Media to President Muhammadu Buhari, on Monday commented on how the list of 2023 presidential aspirants under the All Progressive Congress, (APC) is growing. Recall that ice President Yemi Osinbajo joined the list on Monday by announcing his s intention in a video that was posted on social media, after meeting on Sunday night with the All Progressive Congress (APC) governors informing them of his plans to contest the presidential ticket. Ahmad in a tweet via his official Twitter page wrote, “Bola Tinubu, Dave Umahi, Rochas Okorocha, Yahaya Bello, Rotimi Amaechi, and Yemi Osinbajo. “The list is getting longer”.